      "title": "Salesforce Plugin",
      "excerpt": "Salesforce Plugin\n\nSalesforce supports admin and DevOps workflows for metadata, Flow, Apex tests, LWC, CRM data hygiene, release diagnostics, and Salesforce org automation.\n\nConfiguration Keys\n\n Key Required Sensitive Description \n \n SALESFORCE INSTANCE URL Yes No Salesforce instance URL. \n SALESFORCE ACCESS TOKEN Yes Yes OAuth access token for Salesforce APIs. \n SALESFORCE CLIENT ID No No Connected app client ID for refresh token flows. \n SALESFORCE CLIENT SECRET No Yes Connected app client secret for refresh token flows. \n SALESFORCE REFRESH TOKEN No Yes Refresh token for long running Salesforce access. \n\nSetup\n\n1. Create or select a Salesforce connected app.\n2. Configure OAuth scopes for metadata, tooling, API, and CRM workflows the Buddy needs.\n3. Copy the instance URL into SALESFORCE INSTANCE URL.\n4. Add an access token to SALESFORCE ACCESS TOKEN.\n5. Add client ID, client secret, and refresh token when using refresh token access.\n6. Deploy the Buddy.\n7. Verify with sf version and read only org or metadata queries before deployment actions.\n\nRuntime Assets\n\n Installs @salesforce/cli.\n Registers @salesforce/mcp through npx.\n Adds a verification check for the Salesforce CLI.\n\nReferences\n\n Salesforce DX MCP server\n Salesforce CLI",
